Date: Sat 7 Jan 2017
From: Ursula Hofle-Hansen <Ursula.Hofle@uclm.es> [edited]


Regarding ProMED-mail post "Usutu virus - Europe," I would like to draw your attention to the paper: "Usutu virus, Italy, 1996. Emerg Infect Dis. 2013 Feb;19(2):274-7. doi: 10.3201/eid1902.121191. by Weissenböck H1, Bakonyi T, Rossi G, Mani P, Nowotny N.," in which the authors show by analysis of archive samples that Usutu virus had been causing blackbird mortality in Italy as early as 1996.

The abstract states: "Retrospective analysis of archived tissue samples from bird deaths in the Tuscany region of Italy in 1996 identified Usutu virus. Partial sequencing confirmed identity with the 2001 Vienna strain and provided evidence for a much earlier introduction of this virus into Europe than previously assumed."

--
Ursula Höfle
National Centre for Wildlife Research
Instituto de Investigación en Recursos Cinegéticos (CSIC- UCLM)

